  "active_lock_reason": "resolved",
  "body": "When compiling large projects, Buidler can OOM and crash. To reproduce it, try compiling [Kyber's contracts](https://github.com/KyberNetwork/smart-contracts) with Buidler.\r\n\r\nRunning Buidler with `node --max-old-space-size=4096 node_modules/.bin/buidler` is a workaround, as it increases node's max heap size.\r\n\r\nI found that Truffle [used to have the same issue](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/issues/957) and they fixed it. We should investigate what they did. Maybe a launcher that sets that node flag? @cgewecke I saw you commented on that issue. Any idea how to solve this? :)\r\n\r\nThanks @anyhowclick for reporting it!",
