    "body": "@alcuadrado I think it's still a problem at Truffle too ...  the underlying cause there was [running JSON.parse on the compiler output](https://github.com/trufflesuite/truffle/blob/develop/packages/truffle-compile/run.js#L254) which is still done. \r\n\r\nIt *is* possible to address this by passing the compiler output string to a stream reader and composing the object piece by piece. [This](https://github.com/dominictarr/JSONStream) was a really popular solution.  ",
